{{!--
  Equivalence-topology entry. Collapsed by default. Renders only when
  content.equivalenceTopology is non-null (= the trick has a curator-
  authored entry AND the entry is ratified — pending entries are filtered
  at the service layer before reaching this template).

  Each derivation path renders as a row: an ≡ glyph, the reading text,
  a source-label chip, the ADD breakdown (when present), and a role
  badge for non-canonical paths. The canonical-primary row never carries
  a role badge (it would be redundant). Historical / doctrine-locked /
  deprecated roles carry a small badge so the reader knows the row is
  preserved as pedagogical context, not a competing claim.

  Per the four-layer separation: this surface renders curator-authored
  editorial data only; nothing here consumes parser output. The
  canonical published reading remains the primary surface elsewhere
  on the page (semantic notation, operational notation, hero formula).
--}}
{{#if content.equivalenceTopology}}
<section class="content-section trick-equivalence-topology" aria-label="Alternate derivations">
  <details class="trick-equivalence-topology-disclosure">
    <summary class="trick-equivalence-topology-summary">
      <span class="trick-equivalence-topology-summary-title">Alternate derivations</span>
      <span class="trick-equivalence-topology-summary-hint">Click to expand</span>
    </summary>
    <p class="trick-equivalence-topology-context">{{content.equivalenceTopology.summary}}</p>
    <ul class="trick-equivalence-topology-list">
      {{#each content.equivalenceTopology.derivations}}
        <li class="trick-equivalence-topology-row trick-equivalence-topology-row--{{this.role}}">
          <span class="trick-equivalence-topology-glyph" aria-hidden="true">&equiv;</span>
          <span class="trick-equivalence-topology-reading">{{this.reading}}</span>
          <span class="trick-equivalence-topology-source-chip trick-equivalence-topology-source-chip--{{this.source}}">{{this.source}}</span>
          {{#if this.addBreakdown}}
            <code class="trick-equivalence-topology-breakdown">{{this.addBreakdown}}</code>
          {{/if}}
          {{#unless (eq this.role 'canonical-primary')}}
            <span class="trick-equivalence-topology-role-badge trick-equivalence-topology-role-badge--{{this.role}}">{{this.role}}</span>
          {{/unless}}
        </li>
      {{/each}}
    </ul>
  </details>
</section>
{{/if}}
